column3: It will still be included in the pull (commented out) and then end up in the merge commit

> It will still be included in the pull (commented out) and then end up in the merge commit

I'll add an explicit comment to remove it. And if it's still a problem we can change github-merge.py to filter out HTML comments.

I think this is a lot better experience when submitting a PR, I still hope people will remove it, but even so it makes it easier to distinguish the commit message from
